President Speech Pennsylvania, Jan 29 2014
President Barack Obama talked about retirement security at U.S. Steel’s Mon Valley Works plant in West Mifflin, Pennsylvania. After his remarks, he signed a memorandum that directs the Treasury Department to establish “MyRA” retirement savings plan. The president’s trip was part of a two-day tour highlighting initiatives from his State of the Union address.
